Leucocyte number, differential count and sedimentation rate in 9 "classic" childhood infections. (author's transl). A retrospective analysis of absolute numbers in 802 white blood counts and 396 sedimentation rates of 407 children, admitted between 1973-78, with 9 "classic" infections was done and evaluated for diagnostic usefulness. As diagnostic meaningful it was found: Lymphocytosis in pertussis lymphocytopenia and slight increased sedimentation rate in measles